<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: I'm not sure if this is a bug, but it certainly seems odd. <p>
My L50 Priest killed an Ancient red dragon on L71 of Angband, and it dropped.... *nothing*. Is that supposed to be possible? I've never seen that happen before; all the ADs I've killed previously have splattered treasure all over. I was using Manathrust, and there was no water or lava in the area. There was plenty of wide open floor available. Slightly later on the same level, I came across another Ancient red dragon who dropped as expected. 
</p>
<p>
My character's sanity was mildly damaged, so that *might* have been it, but I was watching and I didn't see any fluctuation at the time I encountered the first ARD. 
</p>
<p>
ZV: I've seen Great Wyrms of Foo dropping nothing too. Full sanity. Not that you don't get enough big dragons to pile the treasure ;-), but still odd. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: Did the message "Compressing items" appear at the level creation by any chance? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: No, no messages of that sort. (In addition, I was playing with always small levels, anyway.) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I've seen this in long fights in Erebor.  I always assumed the item limit was hit, and further generated monsters were generated with no items.  In other words, it's an unfortunate consequence of ToME's generating monsters with items instead of generating them at monster death. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: The thing about it is, it was a small level and really not all that much overall loot (or monsters, for that matter) on the level. That's why I wondered if it might be a bug. I'd expect (or at least be resigned to) such an effect on a large level with a huge number of monsters, but this was different. I wish I'd have kept a savefile or at least a screenshot. Ah well. 
</p>
<p>
*SPOILY* 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Don't mark it spoily here. Mark the main thread! (BTW, it's 'Wight' ;-)) 
    </ul>


<p>
Simon: I've had no quest drop when doing the barrows down whight quest. I've had telepathy and tracked down every last monster and stepped on every square, but no filty rag of the whight was dropped. I've had this 3 times, and each time it was a game where I saved game within the quest. 
</p>
<p>
So even quest hooks and objects defined only in code can have a drop problem. The minotaur of the labyrinth and the sandqueen didn't drop too, on occasions. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./AlexShuman">AlexShuman</a></strong>: <a href="./BugReport178">BugReport178</a> is similar to, items were there, but they disappeared due to same bug. 
</p>
